I‐‐SOMETHING HIT ME THERE.

00:33:44,256 --> 00:33:45,957
WELL,
THE PRODUCT THAT WE HAVE

00:33:45,957 --> 00:33:48,360
IS AN INCREDIBLY INNOVATIVE
GUITAR.

00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:51,162
IN FACT, I THINK YOU COULD SAY
IT'S THE MOST INNOVATIVE GUITAR

00:33:51,162 --> 00:33:54,466
IN A CENTURY
OF GUITAR BUILDING.

00:33:54,466 --> 00:33:56,701
NOT ONLY DO THESE GUITARS
LOOK INCREDIBLE...

00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:59,838
(playing guitar chords)

00:34:06,411 --> 00:34:07,679
WHOO!

00:34:07,679 --> 00:34:10,916
THEY SOUND INCREDIBLE.
BUT THAT'S NOT ALL THEY DO.

00:34:10,916 --> 00:34:14,019
THEY DON'T JUST LOOK GOOD.
THEY DON'T JUST SOUND GOOD...

00:34:20,926 --> 00:34:24,195
THEY FOLD IN HALF.

00:34:24,195 --> 00:34:27,899
THEY FOLD IN HALF SO THAT
YOU NEVER HAVE TO TRAVEL AGAIN

00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:29,367
WITHOUT YOUR GUITAR.

00:34:29,367 --> 00:34:32,537
WHAT MAKES THIS WORK
IS THIS PATENTED HINGE.

00:34:32,537 --> 00:34:34,539
AND NOT ONLY
IS THE HINGE PATENTED,

00:34:34,539 --> 00:34:37,208
WHEN WE BUILT THIS GUITAR,
WE HAD TO TOTALLY CHANGE

00:34:37,208 --> 00:34:39,544
THE WAY A GUITAR HAS BEEN MADE
FOR HUNDREDS OF YEARS.

00:34:39,544 --> 00:34:43,315
NOW THE GUITAR IS DESIGNED
TO FIT NEATLY IN A BACKPACK,

00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:45,817
TO FIT SAFELY IN THE OVERHEAD
COMPARTMENT ON AN AIRLINE.

00:34:45,817 --> 00:34:47,752
IT'S DESIGNED
SO YOU COULD THROW

00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:49,754
A HALF A DOZEN OF 'EM
IN THE TRUNK OF YOUR CAR.

00:34:49,754 --> 00:34:51,790
YOU COULD RIDE YOUR BIKE
WITH IT.

00:34:51,790 --> 00:34:54,292
YOU COULD TAKE A WALK WITH IT.
EASILY FITS ON YOUR BACK.

00:34:54,292 --> 00:34:56,494
YOU ALWAYS HAVE YOUR GUITAR
WITH YOU.

00:34:56,494 --> 00:34:58,530
BRING THAT OVER HERE.
I WANT TO DO IT.

00:34:58,530 --> 00:35:00,599
I WANT TO SEE
IF IT STAYS IN TUNE

00:35:00,599 --> 00:35:04,603
OR I HAVE TO RETUNE THE WHOLE
THING EVERY TIME I DO THAT.
(Josh speaks indistinctly)

00:35:04,603 --> 00:35:07,772
'CAUSE TO ME,
THAT WOULD BE A BIG HASSLE.
SO GRAB THE NECK.

00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:09,574
YEAH.
THERE YOU GO.
AND TAKE THE BODY‐‐

00:35:09,574 --> 00:35:12,143
YEAH.
TAKE THE BODY. PUT IT UNDER
YOUR ARMPIT AS SO.

00:35:12,143 --> 00:35:14,112
YEAH.
JUST PUSH AND TWIST.

00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:16,848
OH, I LIKE
THAT LITTLE SNAP THING.
YEAH. AND, UH...

00:35:16,848 --> 00:35:20,151
OKAY. IT WAS IN TUNE, SO LET'S
SEE IF IT'S IN TUNE RIGHT NOW.

00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:24,055
'CAUSE I BET
IT'S NOT GONNA BE IN TUNE.
(Jeff) FOR HOW MUCH?

00:35:24,055 --> 00:35:26,291
(strumming chords)

