SOUNDS THE SAME.

00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:31,997
OKAY, I WILL ADMIT,
THIS THING STAYED IN TUNE.

00:35:31,997 --> 00:35:34,599
I'D BUY IT.
(Robert) JEFF, IS IT PATENTED?

00:35:34,599 --> 00:35:37,702
DO YOU OWN THE PATENT
TO THE NECK HINGE THING?
YES.

00:35:37,702 --> 00:35:40,038
(Barbara) YES.
(Robert) DO YOU HAVE SALES?

00:35:40,038 --> 00:35:42,040
WE LAUNCHED
IN JANUARY/FEBRUARY.

00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:44,042
WE'VE SOLD ABOUT‐‐
WELL, WE'VE SOLD

00:35:44,042 --> 00:35:46,778
ALL THE UNITS WE'VE BUILT,
ABOUT 800 UNITS.

00:35:46,778 --> 00:35:49,814
RIGHT NOW WE'RE GENERATING
A RELATIVELY SMALL AMOUNT

00:35:49,814 --> 00:35:51,783
OF REVENUE BECAUSE WE'RE NOT
BUILDING THEM FAST ENOUGH.

00:35:51,783 --> 00:35:53,885
WHAT WE WANT
ADDITIONAL CAPITAL FOR

00:35:53,885 --> 00:35:56,788
IS TO BUILD OUT THE INVENTORY.
WHAT DID THE 800 UNITS CREATE
IN REVENUE?

00:35:56,788 --> 00:35:59,924
800 UNITS AT, UH,
WHOLESALE PRICE IS ONLY $500.

00:35:59,924 --> 00:36:01,493
THAT'S ABOUT $400,000.

00:36:01,493 --> 00:36:04,829
SO YOU HAVE SALES OF $400,000?

00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,831
HOW MUCH OF THAT
WAS PROFITABLE?

00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:09,768
OH, WE'RE‐‐WE'RE
CASH FLOW NEGATIVE.

00:36:09,768 --> 00:36:13,171
SO, JEFF, IF YOU'RE ASKING
FOR HALF A MILLION DOLLARS...
MM‐HMM.

00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:15,440
FOR 5% OF YOUR BUSINESS...

00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:19,344
CORRECT.
WHICH MAKES THE OVERALL BUSINESS
WORTH $10 MILLION.

00:36:19,344 --> 00:36:23,548
YES. YES.
(O'Leary) AND YOU'VE ONLY SOLD
$400,000 WORTH OF GUITARS.

00:36:23,548 --> 00:36:27,786
RIGHT.
DO YOU SEE ANY
PROBLEM WITH THAT?

00:36:27,786 --> 00:36:31,189
I‐I SEE NO PROBLEM WITH THAT.
I THINK‐‐
I SEE GREED. I SEE GREED.

00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:35,560
WELL, THIS IS A PRODUCT
THAT HAS A 50% GROSS MARGIN.

00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:37,562
THERE ARE
3 MILLION GUITARS SOLD

00:36:37,562 --> 00:36:39,731
JUST IN THE UNITED STATES
EVERY YEAR,

00:36:39,731 --> 00:36:43,034
AND THERE IS ABSOLUTELY
NO REASON WHY ANYBODY

00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,537
THAT BUYS A GUITAR TODAY
WOULDN'T WANT THE FLEXIBILITY

00:36:45,537 --> 00:36:49,140
TO BE ABLE TO FOLD IT IN HALF
AND TAKE IT WITH THEM.
LET ME ASK

00:36:49,140 --> 00:36:52,143
A REALLY SIMPLE QUESTION
BEFORE YOU GO ANY FURTHER.

00:36:52,143 --> 00:36:55,146
I KNOW I LOOK LIKE A HIP
ROCK STAR‐‐I REALIZE THAT‐‐

00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,916
BUT I ACTUALLY DON'T PLAY
THE GUITAR.

00:36:57,916 --> 00:37:00,085
IF THE HINGE IS UNIQUE
AND PATENTED...
MM‐HMM. YEP.

00:37:00,085 --> 00:37:03,521
THERE ARE LOTS OF PEOPLE
THAT MAKE GUITARS ALREADY.
RIGHT.

00:37:03,521 --> 00:37:08,760
WHY NOT LICENSE
THE HINGE IDEA TO THEM,

00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,796
SIT AT HOME,
COLLECT THE ROYALTY,

00:37:11,796 --> 00:37:14,599
WHICH MEANS
THEY JUST SEND YOU THE MONEY

00:37:14,599 --> 00:37:17,068
EVERY TIME THEY SELL ONE‐‐
WELL‐‐

00:37:17,068 --> 00:37:20,105
(O'Leary) WHY AREN'T YOU
DOING THAT?
IT‐‐IT'S EASIER TO GET THEM
TO COME TO THE TABLE

00:37:20,105 --> 00:37:22,107
IF I'VE DEMONSTRATED MARKET
ACCEPTANCE OF THIS PRODUCT.

00:37:22,107 --> 00:37:25,343
ONCE I'VE DEMONSTRATED‐‐
WE HAVE TO BUILD
A WHOLE GUITAR COMPANY‐‐

00:37:25,343 --> 00:37:27,479
I'VE ALREADY DONE IT.
I'VE ALREADY DONE IT.

00:37:27,479 --> 00:37:30,348
I HAVE
COMPLETE MANUFACTURING‐‐
BUT YOU HAVEN'T SOLD ANY YET.

00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:33,384
I HAVE‐‐WE JUST LAUNCHED.
(Robert) JEFF, YOU CONFUSE ME
A LITTLE BIT.

00:37:33,384 --> 00:37:36,387
OKAY.
'CAUSE I'M NOT CLEAR.
I MEAN, ANSWER THIS FOR ME.

00:37:36,387 --> 00:37:39,023
OKAY.
DO YOU WANT TO MAKE
A GREAT GUITAR

00:37:39,023 --> 00:37:41,025
OR DO YOU WANT TO MAKE
A LOT OF MONEY?

00:37:41,025 --> 00:37:43,762
WELL, I WANT TO MAKE
A LOT OF MONEY...
NO, NO, NO, NO.

00:37:43,762 --> 00:37:46,464
BUILDING A GREAT GUITAR.
I DON'T WANT TO MAKE
A GREAT GUITAR.

00:37:46,464 --> 00:37:49,367
I JUST WANT TO MAKE
A LOT OF MONEY.
YOU KNOW‐‐

00:37:49,367 --> 00:37:51,803
AND I THINK YOU HAVE
A GREAT PRODUCT.

00:37:51,803 --> 00:37:54,239
I THINK WE CAN LICENSE IT.

00:37:54,239 --> 00:37:58,209
WHAT WILL YOU SELL ME
THE RIGHTS TO THAT PATENT FOR?

00:37:58,209 --> 00:38:01,913
I WOULD BE INTERESTED IN...

00:38:01,913 --> 00:38:04,783
49%, 51%...

00:38:04,783 --> 00:38:07,552
(Robert) OKAY.
FOR $1 MILLION.

00:38:07,552 --> 00:38:10,188
DO YOU SAY A MILLION?
YES.

00:38:10,188 --> 00:38:12,624
(Harrington) A MILLION.

00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:15,727
<i>JEFF HAS OFFERED THE SHARKS</i>
<i>49% OF THE PATENT</i>

00:38:15,727 --> 00:38:18,163
<i>FOR $1 MILLION.</i>

00:38:18,163 --> 00:38:21,232
JEFF, YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR $1 MILLION NOW.

00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:24,469
I'M HAVING INDIGESTION,
BUT GO ON.
NOBODY KNOWS
THEY CAN'T DO WITHOUT THIS.

00:38:24,469 --> 00:38:27,238
I'LL‐‐I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.
HERE'S HOW IT WORKS.
OKAY.

00:38:27,238 --> 00:38:29,407
IN THE CONTEXT
OF THE GUITAR INDUSTRY,

00:38:29,407 --> 00:38:32,143
YOU'RE A NOTHING‐BURGER STILL.

00:38:32,143 --> 00:38:34,546
I'LL GIVE YOU $500,000
FOR 51% OF THE COMPANY

00:38:34,546 --> 00:38:37,015
THAT OWNS THIS PATENT.

00:38:40,585 --> 00:38:42,654
SO‐‐SO ANSWER THE QUESTION
FOR ME.

00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:45,557
WHY DO I NEED YOU
TO LICENSE THE GUITAR?

00:38:45,557 --> 00:38:48,827
I HAVE TREMENDOUS EXPERIENCE
IN THE LICENSE SPACE.

00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:51,763
YOU <i>WISH</i> I WAS YOUR PARTNER.

00:38:51,763 --> 00:38:54,966
SO YOU SAID YOU HAVE TREMENDOUS
EXPERIENCE DOING LICENSE DEALS.

00:38:54,966 --> 00:38:57,735
JUST HIT ME WITH ONE AS‐‐
I MEAN, FOR‐‐

00:38:57,735 --> 00:39:01,472
MY WHOLE COMPANY THAT SOLD FOR
$3.2 BILLION WAS ALL LICENSES.

00:39:01,472 --> 00:39:05,210
DID‐‐DID YOU SAY $3.2
WITH A "B"?

00:39:05,210 --> 00:39:08,179
YES, I DID.

00:39:08,179 --> 00:39:10,114
♪♪

00:39:19,768 --> 00:39:25,473
<i>KEVIN O'LEARY HAS OFFERED JEFF</i>
<i>$500,000 FOR 51% OF THE PATENT.</i>

00:39:30,101 --> 00:39:33,037
I WON'T GIVE UP 51%.
OKAY.

00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:36,007
WHY? YOU'RE YOUR OWN
WORST ENEMY.
'CAUSE I'M NOT GONNA
GIVE UP CONTROL‐‐

00:39:36,007 --> 00:39:38,843
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.
JEFF, I'M OUT, THEN.

00:39:38,843 --> 00:39:40,178
♪♪

00:39:40,178 --> 00:39:44,549
IF YOU'RE NOT WILLING TO GIVE UP
THE 51%, I'M OUT.

00:39:44,549 --> 00:39:47,218
(O'Leary) I'M GONNA
DEFEND YOU AGAINST YOU.

00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:50,488
THAT'S WHY I WANT 51%.
THAT'S WHY IT'S SO IMPORTANT.
(laughs)

00:39:50,488 --> 00:39:52,490
YOU UNDERSTAND WHY THAT MATTERS?

00:39:52,490 --> 00:39:54,459
YOU HAVE A DIFFERENT VISION.

00:39:54,459 --> 00:39:59,731
YOU NEED A PARTNER THAT ONLY HAS
ONE DIRECTION‐‐CREATING WEALTH.

00:40:01,266 --> 00:40:04,235
KEVIN, IS YOUR‐‐YOUR OFFER
IS $500,000...

00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:06,237
FOR 51%.

00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:10,108
I WOULD GO $250,000 FOR THAT
TO BRING THE TV TO THE TABLE

00:40:10,108 --> 00:40:11,609
ON THIS‐‐THIS OFFER.

00:40:11,609 --> 00:40:15,013
THEN BE MY PARTNER IN THE DEAL.
BUT IT'S A 51%‐‐

00:40:15,013 --> 00:40:17,115
HOW WOULD THAT‐‐CAN YOU TELL ME,
THROUGH YOUR INFOMERCIALS,

00:40:17,115 --> 00:40:20,418
HOW MANY UNITS‐‐HOW‐‐
WHAT‐‐WHAT COULD YOU PUSH?

00:40:20,418 --> 00:40:24,489
YOU COULD SELL
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS.
HE HAS THE POWER OF TELEVISION.

00:40:24,489 --> 00:40:26,491
THAT'S ONE OF THE PARTNERS
YOU GET.
...PORTFOLIO.

00:40:26,491 --> 00:40:29,627
YOU GUYS ARE IN THE‐‐YOU'RE
GOING IN THE WRONG DIRECTION.

00:40:29,627 --> 00:40:32,030
IT'S SO OBVIOUS,
MR. GUITAR GUY

00:40:32,030 --> 00:40:34,666
AND SON WHO HASN'T SAID
ANYTHING YET.

00:40:34,666 --> 00:40:37,869
DO YOU SPEAK?
I DO SPEAK.

00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:41,806
ALL RIGHT, IF I‐‐I'D
BE MORE INTERESTED IF WE‐‐

00:40:41,806 --> 00:40:44,409
IF HE WERE BACK IN.
HE'S HISTORY. HE'S GONE.

00:40:44,409 --> 00:40:46,144
BARBARA?

00:40:46,144 --> 00:40:48,146
I THINK THERE'S A FLY
IN THE OINTMENT.

00:40:48,146 --> 00:40:50,148
I DON'T THINK IT'S SO EASY

00:40:50,148 --> 00:40:52,383
TO CREATE CHANGE
WITH A BIG MANUFACTURER,

00:40:52,383 --> 00:40:55,053
AND WHEN YOU START
SELLING THEM ON THAT HINGE,

00:40:55,053 --> 00:40:56,788
I BET THERE'S GONNA BE

00:40:56,788 --> 00:40:59,557
SOME OTHER LITTLE NUANCE THAT
GETS IN THE WAY OF THE DEAL.

00:40:59,557 --> 00:41:02,460
SO I'M TOO NERVOUS TO BE IN,
SO I'M OUT.

00:41:04,395 --> 00:41:07,765
JEFF, IT DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU WANT.

00:41:10,368 --> 00:41:12,370
I'M OUT.

00:41:15,373 --> 00:41:17,675
<i>THREE SHARKS ARE OUT,</i>

00:41:17,675 --> 00:41:20,678
<i>AND THERE IS ONE OFFER LEFT</i>
<i>ON THE TABLE.</i>

00:41:20,678 --> 00:41:23,014
YES OR NO?

00:41:23,014 --> 00:41:25,750
(laughs) I WOULD ACCEPT
A DEAL, 50/50...
THAT'S NOT THE DEAL‐‐

00:41:25,750 --> 00:41:28,953
AND THEN‐‐AND WE'RE DONE.
THAT'S NOT THE DEAL
ON THE TABLE.

00:41:28,953 --> 00:41:31,422
(Daymond) THAT'S NOT THE DEAL
ON THE TABLE.
OKAY.

00:41:31,422 --> 00:41:32,924
(Robert) YES OR NO?

00:41:32,924 --> 00:41:35,793
I DON'T ACCEPT THE DEAL
THAT'S ON THE TABLE.

00:41:35,793 --> 00:41:38,997
I'M STUNNED OF YOUR GREED,
YOUR ABSOLUTE GREED.

00:41:38,997 --> 00:41:40,665
YOU JUST SAID THAT GREED‐‐

00:41:40,665 --> 00:41:43,735
WANTING TO MAKE MONEY
IS WHAT THIS IS ALL ABOUT.

00:41:43,735 --> 00:41:46,804
YOU HAD AN OPPORTUNITY TO MAKE
MONEY, AND YOU PASSED ON IT.

00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:50,141
THAT'S NOT ALL THIS IS ABOUT.
YOU'RE A TRAGEDY.
YOU'RE A HUMAN TRAGEDY.

00:41:50,141 --> 00:41:52,710
YOU KNOW, YOU'VE GIVEN ME
A LOT TO THINK ABOUT.

00:41:52,710 --> 00:41:55,446
YOU'RE‐‐YOU'RE
BRILLIANT BUSINESS PEOPLE.

00:41:55,446 --> 00:41:58,483
I'M GONNA HAVE TO DECLINE, BUT I
HOPE WE HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY

00:41:58,483 --> 00:42:02,420
TO WORK TOGETHER DOWN THE ROAD
ON THIS PROJECT OR ON OTHERS.
THERE IS NO TOMORROW.

00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:06,257
YOU'RE DEAD TO ME WHEN YOU
SAY NO TO MY DEAL. YOU'RE DEAD.

00:42:06,257 --> 00:42:10,461
YOU'RE GONE. I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO YOU ARE. YOU'RE A VAPOR.

00:42:10,461 --> 00:42:13,331
JEFF, THANKS. I'LL SEND YOU
AN INVOICE FOR MY TIME.

00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:22,040
UNBELIEVABLE. UNBELIEVABLE.
I TOLD YOU SO.

00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:25,410
WOULD HAVE BEEN A BIG DEAL.
THAT WAS PAINFUL. PAINFUL.

00:42:25,410 --> 00:42:29,147
(O'Leary) UNBELIEVABLE.
THAT GUY HAD A REAL SHOT
AT MAKING MONEY AND SAID NO.

00:42:29,147 --> 00:42:32,617
THIS COULD BE $100 MILLION
ON TV. $100 MILLION.
THAT WAS PAINFUL.

00:42:32,617 --> 00:42:35,153
THAT IS A HUMAN TRAGEDY,
AND HE'S TEACHING HIS SON THAT.

00:42:35,153 --> 00:42:37,588
IT'S A CRIME.
HE SHOULD BE ARRESTED.

00:42:37,588 --> 00:42:40,591
THEY'RE VERY SMART TO ASK
FOR THE DEAL THEY DID.

00:42:40,591 --> 00:42:45,063
AND HOPEFULLY, I WAS
JUST AS SMART TO SAY NO.
OF COURSE YOU WERE.

00:42:45,063 --> 00:42:47,065
TIME WILL TELL.
ASK ME 12 MONTHS FROM NOW

00:42:47,065 --> 00:42:49,200
WHETHER OR NOT IT WAS
THE RIGHT DECISION. (laughs)

00:42:55,440 --> 00:42:57,141
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "SHARK TANK"...</i>

00:42:57,141 --> 00:42:59,977
WHAT IF I GAVE YOU $450,000?
NO.

00:42:59,977 --> 00:43:01,646
$500,000?

00:43:01,646 --> 00:43:04,248
TAKE THE MONEY,
YOU CRAZY CHICKENS.

00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:07,085
THIS DEAL THAT YOU'RE
OFFERING ME IS A SHARK DEAL.

00:43:07,085 --> 00:43:09,120
(singsongy) OH, REALLY?
GUESS WHAT.

00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,155
I DIDN'T WANT TO GET ORDERS
AND PROMISE DELIVERY

00:43:11,155 --> 00:43:13,991
UNTIL I HAD THE CAPITAL
TO GET 'EM DONE.
WHAT YOU JUST SAID
WAS UN‐AMERICAN!

00:43:13,991 --> 00:43:16,661
ON THAT NOTE, I'M OUT.
BUT‐‐BUT‐‐BUT‐‐BUT‐‐BUT WAIT.

00:43:16,661 --> 00:43:18,463
THE NEXT GUY'S
GONNA WALK IN HERE

00:43:18,463 --> 00:43:20,698
AND GET MY MONEY,
AND HE'LL GET RICH, BUT NOT YOU.

00:43:20,698 --> 00:43:23,668
YOU ARE DEAD TO ME
IF YOU TURN AROUND.
OH, MY.

